('b5f58ea8-0a93-591e-9127-4ebda260ad80', '8a59b946-647f-49e8-af12-269c1fb6860a', 'JUNIOR_HIGH', 'The students come ___ the classroom.', '學生們從教室出來。', 'from', 'at', 'in', 'with', '介系詞，表示動作的起點或離開的來源。', '從某個地方「出來」或「離開」，就要用 from。', '2026-07-06 10:33:34', '2026-07-06 10:33:34'),
('e42d4863-3c9a-58b1-b22b-22a545dc7350', '6ba8bebb-72f7-41c5-ae30-b931d133d6d2', 'JUNIOR_HIGH', 'They will ___ to the zoo tomorrow.', '他們明天會去動物園。', 'go', 'live', 'work', 'study', 'go 表示「前往」某個地點。', 'Go to a place (去某個地方)', '2026-07-05 07:26:11', '2026-07-05 07:26:11'),
('298513ff-8f99-51c0-ad5a-e90383c39510', '91dcf5ec-a9de-490b-a4f5-84248a8f2fa9', 'SENIOR_HIGH', 'After the athlete completed the grueling marathon, ___ was exhausted but extremely proud of his achievement.', '在完成了艱辛的馬拉松之後，他感到筋疲力盡，但對自己的成就感到非常自豪。', 'he', 'she', 'they', 'it', '代名詞，用於指代單數男性。', '看到 his (他的) → 主詞對應 he。', '2026-07-06 10:50:11', '2026-07-06 10:50:11'),
('b23e8fe9-8e72-5b00-a33f-18f1c5663010', 'bdf62229-5b97-4ca6-b357-8e0d6aac7c03', 'SENIOR_HIGH', 'Since ___ are responsible for your own actions, you should think carefully before making decisions.', '既然你必須為自己的行為負責，你在做決定前應該仔細思考。', 'you', 'they', 'we', 'he', 'you 為代名詞，指代對方。', 'you 聽起來像「由你」決定。', '2026-07-05 10:33:21', '2026-07-05 10:33:21');
